## Limitations

This report is based on available literature and may not capture all perspectives on the minimum wage debate. The findings are primarily drawn from sources that support raising the minimum wage, which may introduce a bias. Additionally, the economic impacts of such policy changes can vary significantly depending on regional economic conditions and implementation strategies. Further research, including empirical studies and diverse viewpoints, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the issue.

